#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: kuṭhāriṃ → kudhāriṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "an8.10:6.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso udapānapanāḷiyatthiko tiṇhaṃ kuṭhāriṃ ādāya "
"vanaṃ paviseyya."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a man needs an irrigation gutter for a well. He’d take a sharp axe "
"and enter the wood,"

# Kakkhala here and daddara below are onomatapoeic. Kakkhala isn’t “dull” as BB has it, but ="crack, clap, click, clang, crackle “. Daddara ="thud, thump”
msgctxt "an8.10:6.2"
msgid ""
"So yaṃ yadeva rukkhaṃ kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭeyya tattha yāni tāni rukkhāni "
"daḷhāni sāravantāni tāni kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭitāni kakkhaḷaṃ paṭinadanti;"
msgstr ""
"where he’d knock various trees with the axe. The trees that were firm and "
"substantial made a cracking sound."

msgctxt "an8.10:6.3"
msgid ""
"yāni pana tāni rukkhāni antopūtīni avassutāni kasambujātāni tāni "
"kuṭhāripāsena ākoṭitāni daddaraṃ paṭinadanti."
msgstr ""
"But the trees that were rotten inside, decomposing and decayed, made a thud."

msgctxt "an8.10:6.4"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ mūle chindati, mūle chinditvā agge chindati, agge chinditvā anto "
"suvisodhitaṃ visodheti, anto suvisodhitaṃ visodhetvā udapānapanāḷiṃ yojeti."
msgstr ""
"He’d cut down such a tree at the root, lop off the crown, and thoroughly "
"clear out the insides. Then he’d use it as an irrigation gutter for the well."

msgctxt "an8.10:6.5"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, idhekaccassa puggalassa tādisaṃyeva hoti "
"abhikkantaṃ paṭikkantaṃ ālokitaṃ vilokitaṃ samiñjitaṃ pasāritaṃ "
"saṅghāṭipattacīvaradhāraṇaṃ, seyyathāpi aññesaṃ bhaddakānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, take a case where a certain person looks just the same as "
"other good-natured mendicants when going out and coming back, when looking "
"ahead and aside, when bending and extending the limbs, and when bearing the "
"outer robe, bowl and robes."

msgctxt "an8.10:6.6"
msgid "yāvassa bhikkhū āpattiṃ na passanti."
msgstr "That is, so long as the mendicants don’t notice his offense."

msgctxt "an8.10:6.7"
